An R package with FAO, USDA, STATCAN and ISAAA data

Data Sources

  • FAO Food and Agriculture Organization of the United Nations fao.org/faostat/
  • STATCAN Statistics Canada statcan.gc.ca/
  • USDA United States Department of Agriculture usda.gov/
  • ISAAA International Service for the Acquisition of Agri-biotech Applications isaaa.org/

Instalation

Use the following code to install the agdata package in R

devtools::install_github("derekmichaelwright/agData")
library(agData)

theme_agData

xx <- data.frame(x = 1:10, y = 1:10, color = rep(c("1","2"), times = 2, each = 5))
mp <- ggplot(xx, aes(x = x, y = y, color = color)) + 
  geom_point(size = 4) + facet_grid(.~color)
mp

mp + theme_agData()

mp + theme_agData(legend.position = "none")

mp + theme_agData(linesize = 1.5, rotx = T,
                  bgFill = alpha("darkgreen",0.2), 
                  stripFill = alpha("darkred",0.2),
                  lineColor = "darkorange")

##    Area        Crop                             Year `Area harvested` Production  Yield
##    <fct>       <fct>                           <dbl>            <dbl>      <dbl>  <dbl>
##  1 Afghanistan Apples                           1961             2220      15100  6.80 
##  2 Afghanistan Apricots                         1961             4820      32000  6.64 
##  3 Afghanistan Barley                           1961           350000     378000  1.08 
##  4 Afghanistan Cotton lint                      1961               NA      17000 NA    
##  5 Afghanistan Cottonseed                       1961               NA      34000 NA    
##  6 Afghanistan Figs                             1961             3200       8000  2.5  
##  7 Afghanistan Grapes                           1961            50000     225000  4.5  
##  8 Afghanistan Linseed                          1961            46800      17000  0.363
##  9 Afghanistan Maize                            1961           500000     700000  1.4  
## 10 Afghanistan Melons, other (inc.cantaloupes)  1961             3300      15700  4.76 
## # ... with 587,204 more rows
# Prep data for an example plot
xx <- xx %>% filter(Area == "World", Crop == "Lentils", Measurement == "Production")
# Plot
mp <- ggplot(xx, aes(x = Year, y = Value/1000000, group = Area)) + 
  geom_line() + 
  theme_agData() +
  labs(title = "Global Lentil Production", 
       y = "million tonnes", x = NULL)
ggsave("agData_Intro_01.png", mp, width = 6, height = 4)
